<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>1) I do not believe for a second you created your enchanter for the sole purpose of charming, or dealing damage.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I am afraid that charm is the ONLY reason I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>made</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> an enchanter, after watching a level 30 something one take out spectre island in oasis when my 40 something pally couldn't take out one. Charm is not now the only reason, though it is certainly a large part of, I play an enchanter as my main, I also have a 65 cleric, a 65 necro and my orignal pally is now 62, but the enchanter is by far the funnest to play for me simply because of their diversity.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>2) Even if you did, you are by far the minority of enchanters. Thats like a mage saying they created their character to summon food. Charming never was and never will be the main focus of the class.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That is utter bullshit and you know it! I know we are never going to agree on this but Charm is an enchanters core ability, alongside damage mitigation, much like mages pets and nukes. Removing our charm would be akin to removing your nukes.<br>
<br>
Skipping 3, made no sense.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>4)It has always been collectively understood the enchanters main role was in crowd control, or more specificly in minimizing the rate at which foes deal damage. Enchanters do this the best, there is no arguing this fact. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Wrong! Crowd control is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>one</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of our main roles, besides charm in many zones is often one of the only form's of crowd control! ie, unmezzable/unrootable mobs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Instead, im going to flip right back to the last page in my book and get out my hammer spell and GO TO TOWN! <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Talk about flawed logic! You would be laughed at and rightly so. The difference here is that clerics are not tanks, were never meant to be and are unlikey ever to be. I am sure that if you could show people that you could tank better than any warrior they would be in awe of you. Get real! On the other hand enchanters are THE best damage dealers in the game and one of the best damage mitigators. EQ gives us the tools to do both. NB. I am not stating that this is right or fair but it is the reason I play an enchanter.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Fine you know what Im tired of the argument. Forget it Magicians no matter what we say we make it look like class envy. All I have to say is if CoD stays as is I want as a Magician to balance it out is Slow and Our charm and mez spell level cap increased to what the Enchanters charm is. Now if any of you enchanters have a problem with that I want a damn good reason why? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Nothing wrong at all with healthy discussions/arguments just so long as people stick to the facts. Problem is the facts get twisted, exagerated and then half truths get added then just plain lies. Starting with a few uber enchanters soloing some named mobs, but by now we can all do it in our sleep and with both hands tied behind our backs. <br>
<br>
In the real eq world ie. average gear and hp, CoD is (IMHO)reasonably well balanced, since I got it I am having a LOT of fun, but am dying lots also. Yes I have tried some BoT named solo, score so far stands at BoT 5 me 0. What we have done is taken down some with a full group as support where the group would have had no hope of obtaining the drops without CoD, leaving them for more &quot;uber&quot; players than us. If you call that game breaking then so be it, but I am finding it refreshing.<br>
<br>
At the end of the day all I want in EQ is to have fun, and am in favor of any class having abilities necessary to be able to do similar stuff to me, as long as I have a challenge and a way to achieve it I am happy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
